  <body>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <h1 class="text-center"><span class="font-bold">Theme and Variations</span></h1>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <!-- <div class="content"> -->
              <h2 class="text-center">Generate a <span class="font-normal">Musical Composition</span> with Python.</h2>
            <!-- </div> -->
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row new-row">
          <div class="col-md-8">
            <p class="lead">
              Theme and Variations is a traditional musical form where a main melody – the theme – is transformed over and over again to create
              a complete composition.
             </p>
             <p class="lead">
              Here's how Wikipedia describes its history:
              <blockquote>
                "Court dances were long; the tunes which accompanied them were short. Their repetition became intolerably wearisome,
                and inevitably led the player to indulge in extempore variation and ornament"
              </blockquote>
            </p>
            <p class="lead">
              Typically, the theme is first stated in an <span class="font-semi-bold">unaltered form</span>. Then, with the theme now in the listener's ear,
              the composer begins to vary instrumentation, tempo, key, harmony, and other aspects of the music.
              From this simple first statement, a <span class="font-semi-bold">full composition can emerge</span> as the theme is varied.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-4">
            <img class="img-responsive" src="${request.static_url('theme_and_variations:static/beethoven.jpeg')}" alt="pyramid web framework">
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row new-row">
          <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
            <h2>Let's make a Theme and Variations composition!</h2>
            <p class="lead"> Click the button below and one will be generated for you.</p>
            <a href="/generated" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Generate Composition</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row new-row">
          <div class="col-md-12">
            <h2 class="text-center">When you click the button, here's what happens: </h2>
            <p class="lead">1. Random numbers are generated, which are mapped using the <a href="http://www.datasounds.org/" target="_blank">DataSounds</a> library in Python onto musical notes in the key of C.</p>
            <p class="lead">2. This theme is then transformed into different keys, scales, timing, instruments, and it's even reversed.</p>
            <p class="lead">3. After these variations are complete, the musical segments are stitched together into a MIDI file, which simulates the tone of instruments.</p>
            <p class="lead">4. Finally, the composition is delivered to you to download and listen to. You'll need a MIDI player like GarageBand to listen. If it sounds really bad, try again – some compositions are more musical than others!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="copyright text-center">
            Made by Zach Caceres for <a href="#" target="_blank">Python-a-thon</a> 2016.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

